of an annuity is a scheduled set of payments that exist for a predetermined period of time the schedule for and amount of the annuity payments will rely largely on your retirement goals and the period of time until you retire  once you have made your scheduled payments or investments you will be able to begin receiving payments  these disbursements will serve as your retirement income  many people prefer annuities for retirement because they come in many flexible options and they provide a guaranteed income upon retirement the main types are immediate  allow you to be paid a set amount of money on a predetermined schedule fixed period annuities  are a more conservative option and come with a minimum interest rate guaranteed equityindexed  give you the opportunity to earn a higher rate of return variable annuities  the most flexible annuity and are subject to rises similar to stocks bonds or mutual funds from our customers your response was super timely and the agents to whom i spoke were very professional and helpful martha lewallen south bend in insurance corner  states will sue over health care bill passage thu  feb  —  states will sue over health care bill passageposted on mon march  news states will sue over health care bill read more  to go down as costly year for weather disasters thu  feb  —  to go down as costly year for weather disastersposted on thu january  news to go down as costly year for read more read more articles find information and get free insurance quotes fixed period annuities these are annuities that offer a set period of time for payback usually in ranges of  years  more information on fixed annuities variable annuities these are annuities that the money is invested into a mutual fund managed by the company  growth depends on the performance of the funds  more information on variable annuities nonqualified annuities these are annuities that are purchased through a tax deferred account but are not tax deductable and taxes must be paid on the income  more information on nonqualified annuities life annuities these are annuities that payout until the person is no longer alive  more information on life annuities qualified annuities these are annuities that are purchased through a tax deferred account such as a k and are tax deductable  more information on qualified annuities single premium annuities these annuities require an up front lump sum of money to get going  more information on single premium annuities get free insurance quotes and save zip code quote type auto insurance health insurance home insurance life insurance long term care disability insurance annuities group insurance commercial auto start quote now   get more quotes home faq terms of use privacy policy site map affiliates insurance leads     all web leads inc all rights reserved all trademarks are the property of their respective holders   fm  bldg  suite  austin tx   phone  lincoln life annuities  web  mailcom web news images videos search ads by yahoo related to lincoln life annuities annuity  life insurance  brighthouse financial learn the difference between annuities  life insurance  talk to your advisor wwwbrighthousefinancialcom related searches lincoln life annuities lincoln life annuities signin lincoln national life annuities lincoln life variable annuities lincoln benefit life annuities lincoln life and annuities lincoln life insurance annuities mailcom privacy policy about mailcom technology copyright    mail  media inc all rights reserved cookies help us deliver our services by using our services you agree to our use of cookies ok learn more referencecom  whats your question wwwreferencecom articles what is a variable annuity a variable annuity is a retirement account that allows a person to choose her investments and the annuity provides an income based on how well the investments are doing in the stock and bond markets explains cnn a var more » wwwreferencecom › business  finance › investing what are lincoln benefit life ann